      "id": "PopularPost355564",
      "post_content": "Oracle is just about as clunky as the original printed rules text on this one. But it has its uses. Two mana can deal a lot of damage to someone who uses big-damage sorceries. Follow up somebody's [Hurricane](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hurricane) with this and you might knock them out.  \n  \nIt's probably not worth putting in any maindeck, but it's more playable than a lot of its set and its contemporaries, when flavor drove design at the expense of sound game mechanics.",
